{
  "texts": [
    "Across all cases, the optimal angle lies between 51°and 54.2°.",
    "The lowest value, 51.12°, is obtained for an inlet velocity of 10 mm/s.",
    "For both higher and lower inlet velocities, the optimal angle is slightly larger.",
    "The relative improvement ranges from 7.5% to 5.5%, decreasing with increasing feeding rates.",
    "To better understand the flow inside the nozzle, we looked at the flow fields with the streamlines for the case with the inlet velocity of 10 mm/s (Fig. 8)."
  ]
}